This paper deals with the construction of graph spanners, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various fields such as network design and routing. The paper proposes a new algorithm for constructing roundtrip spanners in directed graphs, which is a specific type of spanner that preserves roundtrip distances. This problem is closely related to topics in computational geometry (cs.CG), graph algorithms (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and game theory (cs.GT). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
